ation on natural history and conservation. Sara Lourie, a foremost expert on seahorse taxonomy, presents captivating stories of species that range from less than an inch to over a foot in height, while highlighting recent discoveries and ecological concerns. Accessibly written, but comprehensive in scope, this book will be a stunning and invaluable reference on seahorse evolution, biology, habitat, and behavior. Masters of camouflage and rarely seen, seahorses continue to be a fascinating subject of active research. This visually rich and informative book is certain to become the authoritative guide to these charming and unusual wonders of the sea, beloved at aquariums the world over.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aSea horses. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aseahorses, marine animals, ocean, reproduction, gender, pregnancy, habitat, species, identification, science, biology, zoology, nonfiction, eggs, hatching, shallow water, conservation, extinct, endangered, populations, environment, environmentalism, seadragons, pipefish, natural history, taxonomy, evolution, ecology, syngnathidae, behavior, morphology, prehensile tail, courtship, mating, pair bonds, fossils, urophori, gastrophori, aquaculture, destructive fishing, red list.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311071098440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226338552423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226338552/original  a978-3-11-071098-4  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles